 Here we have $222$ in base $10$. To get its binary equivalent, we repeatedly divide by $2$ and record the remainders: 
\begin{align*}222&=2\cdot 111+0\\111&=2\cdot 55+1\\55&=2\cdot 27+1\\27&=2\cdot 13+1\\13&=2\cdot 6+1\\6&=2\cdot 3+0\\3&=2\cdot 1+1\\1&=2\cdot0+1\end{align*}
Reading the remainders backward, we have $222_{10}=11011110_2$. The sum of the digits of this expression is $\boxed{5}$ </think> <answer> 5 </answer>

